POLICE in Soweto are investigating an inquest case after three people died mysteriously in Emdeni on Tuesday, 25 May The bodies of a man, woman and child were found in their home, but the details of how they died are yet to be known. Police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Masondo confirmed the incident. He said: “On 25 May, police were called by a landlord who indicated that he arrived home and discovered that his tenants had died. Police proceeded to the scene and found the bodies of a middle-aged man and woman, as well as q toddler. They were all certified dead by paramedics. “Police are investigating the circumstances that led to their deaths. An inquest docket has since been opened pending further investigation and postmortem results.”